name: The Magician
note:
\fi[Sky Pirate]\fr\} At certain locations on the map, Elsa can use her ship to travel from location to location quickly. When Elsa slays a Player or a Boss enemy, she gains an additional Star. If Elsa has traded with that Player before, she gains another additional Star once.
\fr\fi[Ark Royal]\fr\} Elsa begins the game with the Blue Spellbook. Her Basic Attacks deal bonus damage equal to 10% of Ability Power. Increase Munny Gain by 20%.
\fr\fi[King Slayer]\fr\} Elsa deals 50% increased damage to Boss enemies and to the Player with the most Stars in the game that is not her.

name: The Emperor
note:
\fi[Perfect Evolution]\fr\} After slaying an Objective, Player, or Boss, increase all Base Stats by 1.
\fr\fi[Perfect Path]\fr\} Nova gains 2 Stars every 20 Levels.
\fr\fi[Perfect Form]\fr\} Nova gains 10% Physical and Magical Lifesteal. After battle, Nova regenerates 10% of his HP.

name: The Hierophant
note:
\fi[Son√≠do]\fr\} Mercury gains Attack Damage and Ability Power equal to 10% of her Speed.
\fr\fi[Cazadora]\fr\} After slaying an enemy, immediately gain 1 Stage of Attack Damage for 5 turns and restore 15% of her missing HP and MP(min. 3% max HP/MP).
\fr\fi[Hierro]\fr\} If Mercury deals damage to an enemy, until the end of the turn, that enemy deals 10-40% reduced total damage to Mercury, increased based on the difference in Speed between Mercury and the foe.
\fr\fi[Primera Bestia]\fr\} When Mercury defeats a Creep, she can freely convert it into a Minion. If the Minion slays a Player, Mercury gains 2 Stars.

name: The Lover
note:
\fi[Toxic Love]\fr\} When attacking an enemy afflicted by a Negative Status Effect, increase damage dealt by 30% and reduce damage taken from that enemy by 30%, increasing per consecutive action during a turn.. This effect is halved against non-Player enemies.
\fr\fi[Scum of the Earth]\fr\} Monarch can sabotage Chests for free, as well as create her own fake Chests. Enemies who open the Sabotaged Chests immediately take 20% of their maximum HP in true damage and take 20% of their missing HP over a duration. If the enemy dies by either effect, Monarch gains 2 Stars.

name: Death
note:
\fi[Inhuman Fucking Monster]\fr\} At the start of the game, Joker can transform her appearance and nameplate to another character. While transformed, Joker can falsify her HP, MP, and Momentum values. This effect ends when Joker enters combat with another Player.
\fr\fi[Shadow Tag]\fr\} Enemies cannot escape from Joker.
\fr\fi[Manipulator]\fr\}\} Joker has a personal item called 'Authority of Death'. She can place a bet that 1 Player in the game will kill another specific player. If this bet comes true, Joker gains 3 Stars from both players and kills them both. Joker can promote and end the game off this Star gain. Joker cannot bet on 2 players already in combat with each other and cannot change her bet for 7 minutes. \fi\fb\}[Joker is afflicted with the following demerits in exchange for her power.]\fr
\fr\fi\}-Joker has no Tailwind or Rebound Gauge. Events that would fill these Gauges instead restore her HP and MP respectively.
\fr\fi\}-Joker cannot initiate combat with Players, except for Diety tier enemies.
\fr\fi\}-When Joker would lose Stars, double the amount lost.(Up to a bonus loss of 2 additonal Stars)
\fr\fi\}-Stat Buff/Debuffs on Joker cannot be stacked.
\fr\fi\}-Joker's Element Type is Ankh. This cannot be changed.

name: Temperance
note:
\fi[download()]\fr\} On battle start, gain 1 Stage of either Attack Damage or Ability Power based on the weaker of first opponent's defensive stats. Also gain 1 of either Defense or Magic Resist based on the higher of the first opponent's offensive stats. These buffs last for 3 turns.
\fr\fi[stance_change()]\fr\}\} Etranger can enter difference Stances during combat. When entering Stances, restore 20% missing HP.
\fr\fi-[Overcharged]\fr\} Increase AD/AP by 50%. Reduce Def/Res by 50%.
\fr\fi-[Cooled]\fr\} Increase Def/Res by 30%. Reduce AD/AP by 30%.
\fr\fi-[Turbo Mode]\fr\} Increase Speed by 200%. At the end of each turn, lose 10% max HP.

name: The Devil
note:
\fi[Bloodstained Diva]\fr\} Aaroy gains 20% Physical Lifesteal and Magical Lifesteal.

\fr\fi[True Villain]\fr\} Aaroy's location cannot be located by enemies with items, nor can her current equipment or Stars be viewed by anyone but her. Aaroy cannot initiate combat with any Player within the first 10 minutes of the game. \fi\fb\}[Aaroy gains additional Stars when defeating another Player. The bonus increases based on the victim's tier before death. Aaroy does not gain additional Stars if the victim was a lower tier than her.]\fr
\fr\fi\}-Bronze-Silver: +1
\fr\fi\}-Gold-Diamond: +2
\fr\fi\}-Diety: +3. If the foe was Diety tier, the Star Gain can Promote and end the game.

\fr\fbAaroy gains 5% Total Damage Reduction for every Tier above Bronze she is in(up to 25% in Diety Tier).

name: The Star
note:
\fi[Avenger]\fr\} When slain by another player, killing that player will grant an additional 2 Stars. Can promote and end the game with this promotion.
\fr\fi[Mercurial]\fr\} Instead of a normal Spellbook, Clear comes equipped with the Orchid Spellbook. She is normal type by default, but when casting a Skill, changes type to match Skill being cast.
\fr\fi[Precognition]\fr\} Critical Strike Chance is doubled. Critical Strikes reduce the target's Defense by 15% instead of 20%.

name: The Moon
note:
\fi[Conqueror]\fr\} Gain 50% increased Tailwind points. When Auriel earns a Star, restore 50% maximum HP/MP immediately.
\fr\fi[Lord of Execution]\fr\} On enemy death, restore 10 Momentum and 10% of the user's missing HP/MP.(Min. 3% max HP/MP)
